    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That makes sense, but I've seen some people argue that the UN is basically just a tool for powerful countries to maintain their own interests, and that it actually fails at its core mission whenever a major power is involved. Do historians see those kinds of criticisms as valid structural critiques, or is that more of an outsider/fringe perspective?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
