      "content": "Historians widely regard these critiques as valid structural analyses, not fringe views. They often point to the veto power within the Security Council as the primary mechanism that allows great powers to shield allies or pursue self-interests. This inherent structural limitation means the UN's efficacy is fundamentally constrained by geopolitical power dynamics among its most influential members.",
