      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Many contemporary IR scholars argue that while the ideal of perfect collective security is unachievable, the system remains practically necessary. The UN provides indispensable platforms for diplomacy, humanitarian coordination, and establishing international norms, even when it cannot impose rapid, unified military action. It is thus seen less as a guarantor of peace and more as a crucial framework for managing global conflict and promoting international cooperation.",
      "source": "target",
